{
  "text": "As mentioned earlier, the fastest known classical algorithms for TSP on general graphs are the Bellman-Held-Karp algorithm that runs in time O(n 2 2 n log L) and Björklund's algorithm that runs in time O * (1.657 n L) [CITATION_1] . For MSC, there are classical algorithms with running times O(nm2 n ), O(n2 m ) and O(1.227 n+m ) [CITATION_2] . Note that a trivial application of Grover's search results in an O * ( √ 2 m ) quantum algorithm for MSC. The fastest known classical algorithm for Feedback Arc Set runs in time O * (2 n ). Table 1 lists the running times of the algorithms given in this paper. All the algorithms require exponential space as they need to store a partial dynamic programming table. The algorithms return the correct answer with probability at least 2/3. Classical (best known) Quantum (this paper) Path in the Hypercube",
